# Project Understanding Checklist

## Objective
Gain comprehensive understanding of the project's technical composition and architecture.

## Instructions
Complete each item of this checklist step by step to ensure thorough understanding of the project. Do not move to the next item until you have completed the current one. After completing each item mark it as done with an `[x]`.

Document the results of your research for each item, always providing evidence by referencing the relevant files, functions or providing snippets of code.

- [ ] Starting analysis. Make sure the full checklist is saved at the `docs` folder of a project as `project_understanding.md`.

## Language & Framework Analysis 
- [ ] Identify all programming languages used in the project
- [ ] Document frameworks and their versions
- [ ] Note project structure and main componets
- [ ] Where are libraries and configurations stored
- [ ] Review package manager. List main third-party libraries

## Architecture Review
- [ ] Identify architecture paradigm
- [ ] Identify all system components and their interactions
- [ ] Map data flows between components
- [ ] Document data storage locations and types
- [ ] Analyze authentication mechanisms
- [ ] Review authorization mechanisms
- [ ] Document API endpoints and integration points
